WEBVTT



00:00:00.032 --> 00:00:10.080
Leprosy still exists. Every two minutes someone is diagnosed with this disease. In an unjust world, their suffering won't make the headlines. It's hidden in the world's poor world.

00:00:09.600 --> 00:00:19.648
Old, poorest places, the physical effects are devastating. But the hardest part is how you are treated. Even if you've been cured, you can be rejected by your family and community.

00:00:19.168 --> 00:00:29.216
isolated, shamed and forgotten. But God sees and so do we. It's time to end leprosy. To learn more, visit leprosymission.org.uk/leprosymissions

00:00:28.736 --> 00:00:30.368
UK slash Premier.

00:00:30.944 --> 00:00:40.320
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons. This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:00:40.320 --> 00:00:50.368
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way and I'm confident they'll do the same for you. So get ready to be challenged.

00:00:49.888 --> 00:00:58.624
be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the Church.

00:00:59.712 --> 00:01:02.208
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:04.640
A sermon by Charles Spurgeon.

00:01:04.832 --> 00:01:05.984
Part one.

00:01:06.688 --> 00:01:09.312
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:01:09.664 --> 00:01:11.904
John's Gospel, chapter twenty,

00:01:11.648 --> 00:01:13.120
Verse 15

00:01:14.944 --> 00:01:19.360
I was sitting about a fortnight ago in a very lovely garden.

00:01:19.488 --> 00:01:25.376
In the midst of all kinds of flowers which were blooming in delightful abundance all around.

00:01:26.048 --> 00:01:28.992
Screening myself from the heat of the sun

00:01:28.768 --> 00:01:31.840
Under overhanging boughs of an olive tree,

00:01:31.744 --> 00:01:35.648
I cast my eyes upon palms and bananas.

00:01:35.392 --> 00:01:37.504
roses and camellias,

00:01:37.312 --> 00:01:41.024
Oranges and aloes, lavender and heliotrope.

00:01:41.568 --> 00:01:44.544
The garden was full of colour and beauty.

00:01:44.320 --> 00:01:46.688
Perfume and fruitfulness

00:01:46.944 --> 00:01:49.760
Surely the gardener,, whoever they might be,,

00:01:49.728 --> 00:01:54.112
Who had framed and fashioned and kept in order that lovely spot.

00:01:54.016 --> 00:01:56.512
Deserved great commendation.

00:01:57.024 --> 00:01:58.272
So I thought.

00:01:58.816 --> 00:02:02.592
And then it came to me to meditate upon the Church of God.

00:02:02.432 --> 00:02:03.712
As a garden.

00:02:03.872 --> 00:02:07.136
And to suppose the Lord Jesus to be the gardener.

00:02:07.488 --> 00:02:11.904
And then to think of what would most assuredly happen if it were so.

00:02:12.224 --> 00:02:13.920
Supposing him?

00:02:13.856 --> 00:02:15.200
To be the God-man.

00:02:15.424 --> 00:02:22.848
My mind conceived of a paradise where all sweet things flourish and all evil things are rooted up.

00:02:23.424 --> 00:02:26.848
If an ordinary worker had produced such beauty,

00:02:26.592 --> 00:02:29.536
As I then saw and enjoyed on earth,

00:02:29.696 --> 00:02:34.848
What beauty and glory must surely be brought forth, supposing him?

00:02:34.720 --> 00:02:36.032
to be the gardener.

00:02:36.704 --> 00:02:38.624
You know the hymn.

00:02:38.464 --> 00:02:40.000
To whom we refer,

00:02:39.840 --> 00:02:42.272
The ever blessed son of god

00:02:42.528 --> 00:02:45.120
Who marry Magdalene in our text?

00:02:45.120 --> 00:02:47.136
Mistook for the gardener.

00:02:47.424 --> 00:02:51.616
We will for once follow a saint in her mistaken track

00:02:51.744 --> 00:02:55.296
And yet we shall find ourselves going in a right way.

00:02:55.808 --> 00:03:00.608
She was mistaken when she fell into supposing him to be the gardener.

00:03:00.928 --> 00:03:04.288
But if we are under his Spirit's teaching,

00:03:04.064 --> 00:03:06.112
We shall not make a mistake.

00:03:06.080 --> 00:03:12.992
If now we indulge ourselves in a quiet meditation upon our ever-blessed Lord, supposing him.

00:03:12.992 --> 00:03:14.432
To be the gardener.

00:03:15.808 --> 00:03:18.880
It is not an unnatural supposition, surely.

00:03:19.264 --> 00:03:21.824
For if we may truly sing

00:03:21.600 --> 00:03:27.264
We are a garden walled around, chosen and made peculiar ground.

00:03:27.840 --> 00:03:30.592
That enclosure needs a gardener.

00:03:30.784 --> 00:03:34.400
Are we not all the plants of his right-hand planting?

00:03:34.912 --> 00:03:37.120
Do we not all need watering?

00:03:37.056 --> 00:03:40.672
And tending by his constant and gracious care.

00:03:41.056 --> 00:03:42.272
He says,

00:03:42.208 --> 00:03:44.288
I am the true vine

00:03:44.576 --> 00:03:46.816
My father is the husbandman.

00:03:47.008 --> 00:03:48.896
And that is one view of it.

00:03:49.344 --> 00:03:51.360
But we may also sing,

00:03:51.360 --> 00:03:53.184
My well-beloved,

00:03:52.960 --> 00:03:56.096
Hath a vineyard in a very fruitful hill.

00:03:56.000 --> 00:03:57.632
And he fenced it.

00:03:57.472 --> 00:04:02.496
And gathered out the stones thereof, and planted it with the choicest vine.

00:04:03.008 --> 00:04:04.512
That is to say,

00:04:04.480 --> 00:04:07.232
He acted as gardener to it.

00:04:07.872 --> 00:04:13.728
Thus has Isaiah taught us to sing a song of the well-beloved touching his vineyard.

00:04:14.528 --> 00:04:18.016
We read of our Lord just now under these terms,

00:04:17.920 --> 00:04:23.328
Thou that dwellest in the gardens, the companions hearken to thy voice.

00:04:23.968 --> 00:04:27.520
To what purpose does he dwell in the vineyards?

00:04:27.104 --> 00:04:30.432
But that he may see how the vines flourish.

00:04:30.464 --> 00:04:32.832
And care for all the plants.

00:04:33.440 --> 00:04:39.584
The image I say is so far from being unnatural that it is most pregnant with suggestions,

00:04:39.520 --> 00:04:41.856
And full of useful teaching.

00:04:42.528 --> 00:04:45.408
We are not going against the harmonies of nature.

00:04:45.376 --> 00:04:47.488
When we are supposing him,

00:04:47.360 --> 00:04:48.704
to be the gardener.

00:04:49.888 --> 00:04:52.480
Neither is the figure unscriptural.

00:04:52.544 --> 00:04:58.080
For in one of his own parables, our Lord makes himself to be the dresser of the vineyard.

00:04:58.752 --> 00:05:01.312
We read just now that parable,

00:05:01.088 --> 00:05:02.880
So full of mourning.

00:05:03.328 --> 00:05:06.080
When the certain man came in,

00:05:05.824 --> 00:05:09.440
And saw the fig tree that it brought forth no fruit,

00:05:09.472 --> 00:05:12.224
He said unto the dresser of his vineyard,

00:05:12.224 --> 00:05:13.536
Cut it down.

00:05:13.632 --> 00:05:16.064
Why cumbereth it the ground?

00:05:17.088 --> 00:05:22.272
Who was it that intervened between that profitless tree and the axe?

00:05:22.528 --> 00:05:26.048
But our great intercessor and interposer.

00:05:26.848 --> 00:05:28.192
He, it is.

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:30.784
Who continually comes forward with

00:05:30.912 --> 00:05:33.440
Let it alone this year also.

00:05:33.504 --> 00:05:36.256
Till I shall dig about it and dung it.

00:05:36.672 --> 00:05:38.240
In this case,

00:05:37.984 --> 00:05:42.240
He takes upon himself the character of the vine dresser.

00:05:42.496 --> 00:05:44.128
And we are not wrong.

00:05:43.840 --> 00:05:45.600
In supposing him.

00:05:45.568 --> 00:05:47.008
to be the gardener.

00:05:47.904 --> 00:05:50.432
If we would be supported by a type,

00:05:50.592 --> 00:05:53.696
Our Lord takes the name of the second Adam.

00:05:54.048 --> 00:05:56.608
And the first Adam was a gardener.

00:05:56.896 --> 00:05:58.624
Moses tells us:

00:05:58.400 --> 00:06:02.688
that the Lord God placed the man in the Garden of Eden to dress it,

00:06:02.784 --> 00:06:04.160
And to keep it.

00:06:04.864 --> 00:06:07.200
Man in his best estate

00:06:07.136 --> 00:06:11.776
Was not to live in this world in a paradise of indolent luxury.

00:06:12.128 --> 00:06:15.360
But in a garden of recompensed toil.

00:06:16.192 --> 00:06:17.376
Behold,

00:06:17.472 --> 00:06:18.688
The church

00:06:18.656 --> 00:06:20.608
Is Christ's Eden?

00:06:20.672 --> 00:06:23.008
Watered by the river of life.

00:06:22.880 --> 00:06:24.704
And so fertilized.

00:06:24.448 --> 00:06:28.000
That all manner of fruits are brought forth unto God.

00:06:28.448 --> 00:06:29.600
And he,

00:06:29.376 --> 00:06:31.232
Our second Adam.

00:06:31.264 --> 00:06:35.680
walks in this spiritual Eden to dress it and to keep it.

00:06:35.904 --> 00:06:37.664
And so by a type

00:06:37.504 --> 00:06:40.768
We see that we are right in supposing him.

00:06:40.704 --> 00:06:42.176
To be the gardener.

00:06:42.720 --> 00:06:50.880
Thus also Solomon thought of him when he described the royal bridegroom as going down with his spouse to the garden.

00:06:51.072 --> 00:06:56.576
When the flowers appeared on the earth, and the fig tree had put forth her green figs,

00:06:56.864 --> 00:06:58.208
He went out,

00:06:57.984 --> 00:06:59.488
With his beloved,

00:06:59.520 --> 00:07:02.272
For the preservation of the gardens,

00:07:02.176 --> 00:07:03.264
Saying,

00:07:03.360 --> 00:07:08.352
Take us, the foxes, the little foxes that spoil the vines,

00:07:08.640 --> 00:07:11.360
For our vines have tender grapes.

00:07:12.096 --> 00:07:15.488
Neither nature nor scripture, nor type,

00:07:15.712 --> 00:07:16.928
Nor song,

00:07:16.992 --> 00:07:20.736
forbids us to think of our adorable Lord Jesus.

00:07:20.512 --> 00:07:24.416
As one who cares for the flowers and fruits of his church.

00:07:24.736 --> 00:07:26.272
We err not.

00:07:26.176 --> 00:07:29.888
When we speak of him, supposing him to be the gardener.

00:07:30.784 --> 00:07:32.640
And so I sat still.

00:07:32.640 --> 00:07:35.808
And indulge the suggested line of thought,

00:07:35.648 --> 00:07:37.920
Which I now repeat in your hearing.

00:07:37.920 --> 00:07:42.848
Hoping that I may open many roads of meditation for your hearts also.

00:07:43.360 --> 00:07:47.392
I shall not attempt to think out such a subject thoroughly

00:07:47.328 --> 00:07:51.040
But only to indicate in which direction you may look.

00:07:50.816 --> 00:07:53.344
For a veil of precious ore.

00:07:54.912 --> 00:07:56.608
Supposing him,

00:07:56.416 --> 00:07:57.856
To be the gardener.

00:07:57.952 --> 00:07:59.456
We have here

00:07:59.296 --> 00:08:01.920
The key to many wonders.

00:08:01.728 --> 00:08:03.776
In the garden of his church.

00:08:04.224 --> 00:08:09.056
The first wonder is that there should be a church at all in the world.

00:08:09.088 --> 00:08:13.792
That there should be a garden blooming in the midst of this sterile waste.

00:08:14.240 --> 00:08:17.280
Upon a hard and flinty rock

00:08:17.536 --> 00:08:21.152
The Lord has made the Eden of his church to grow.

00:08:21.920 --> 00:08:24.032
How did it come to be here?

00:08:24.128 --> 00:08:27.104
An oasis of life in a desert of death?

00:08:27.552 --> 00:08:29.216
How pale faith

00:08:28.992 --> 00:08:30.976
In the midst of unbelief,

00:08:31.104 --> 00:08:32.224
And hope,

00:08:32.224 --> 00:08:34.592
Where all is servile fear.

00:08:35.040 --> 00:08:36.224
And love.

00:08:36.192 --> 00:08:38.144
Where hate abounds.

00:08:38.912 --> 00:08:41.696
Ye are of God's little children.

00:08:41.792 --> 00:08:45.536
And the whole world lieth in the wicked one.

00:08:46.880 --> 00:08:49.760
From where came this being of God?

00:08:49.728 --> 00:08:52.448
Where all else is wrapped up in the devil.

00:08:52.992 --> 00:08:58.688
How did there come to be a people for God, separated and sanctified?

00:08:58.464 --> 00:09:00.192
And consecrated.

00:09:00.032 --> 00:09:01.472
And ordained.

00:09:01.152 --> 00:09:04.128
To bring forth fruit unto his name.

00:09:04.672 --> 00:09:11.040
Assuredly, it could not have been so at all if the doing of it had been left to men and women.

00:09:11.808 --> 00:09:14.592
We understand its existence

00:09:14.432 --> 00:09:16.256
Supposing him

00:09:16.256 --> 00:09:17.824
To be the gardener,

00:09:18.560 --> 00:09:21.312
But nothing else can account for it.

00:09:22.208 --> 00:09:24.864
He can cause the fir tree

00:09:24.608 --> 00:09:27.168
To flourish instead of the thorn.

00:09:27.296 --> 00:09:28.608
And the myrtle,

00:09:28.448 --> 00:09:30.112
Instead of the brier.

00:09:30.656 --> 00:09:34.176
But no one else can accomplish such a change.

00:09:35.072 --> 00:09:37.152
The garden in which I sat,

00:09:37.056 --> 00:09:39.648
Was made on the bare face of the rock.

00:09:39.616 --> 00:09:43.648
And almost all the earth of which its terraces were composed.

00:09:43.552 --> 00:09:46.720
Had been brought up there from the shore below.

00:09:46.912 --> 00:09:48.544
By hard labour.

00:09:49.120 --> 00:09:50.752
And so upon the rock,

00:09:50.752 --> 00:09:53.120
A soil had been created.

00:09:53.504 --> 00:09:54.688
It was not.

00:09:54.464 --> 00:09:58.368
By its own nature that the garden was found in such a place.

00:09:58.528 --> 00:10:01.824
But by skill and labour it had been formed.

00:10:01.920 --> 00:10:04.224
Even so, the Church of God,

00:10:03.936 --> 00:10:06.176
Has had to be constructed

00:10:05.984 --> 00:10:07.744
By the Lord Jesus,

00:10:07.872 --> 00:10:11.808
Who is the author as well as the perfecter of his garden?

00:10:12.320 --> 00:10:13.472
Painfully.

00:10:13.504 --> 00:10:15.648
With wounded hands,

00:10:15.584 --> 00:10:18.016
Has he built each terrace?

00:10:17.856 --> 00:10:20.032
And fashioned each bed.

00:10:20.128 --> 00:10:22.464
And planted each plant.

00:10:23.264 --> 00:10:24.960
All the flowers

00:10:24.704 --> 00:10:28.064
Have had to be watered with his bloody sweat.

00:10:28.288 --> 00:10:31.360
And watched by his tearful eyes.

00:10:31.584 --> 00:10:38.080
The nail-prints in his hands and the wound in his side are the tokens of what it cost him.

00:10:38.048 --> 00:10:40.896
To make a new paradise.

00:10:41.472 --> 00:10:43.392
He has given his life,

00:10:43.296 --> 00:10:46.816
For the life of every plant that is in the garden.

00:10:46.912 --> 00:10:48.384
And not one of them.

00:10:48.384 --> 00:10:51.104
Has been there on any other theory,

00:10:50.912 --> 00:10:52.928
Than supposing him.

00:10:53.056 --> 00:10:54.496
To be the gardener.

00:10:56.000 --> 00:10:57.184
Besides,

00:10:57.056 --> 00:10:58.656
There is another wonder.

00:10:58.880 --> 00:11:02.976
How comes the Church of God to flourish in such a climate?

00:11:03.872 --> 00:11:08.736
This present evil world is very uncongenial to the growth of grace.

00:11:09.280 --> 00:11:12.800
And the church is not able by herself alone.

00:11:12.864 --> 00:11:16.928
To resist the evil influences which surround her.

00:11:17.600 --> 00:11:23.456
The Church contains within itself elements which tend to its own disorder.

00:11:23.296 --> 00:11:25.664
And destruction if left alone.

00:11:25.888 --> 00:11:27.584
Even as the garden,

00:11:27.360 --> 00:11:29.600
Has present in its soil.

00:11:29.696 --> 00:11:33.376
All the germs of a tangled thicket of weeds.

00:11:34.592 --> 00:11:38.080
The best church that ever Christ had on earth.

00:11:37.856 --> 00:11:40.160
Would within a few years

00:11:39.968 --> 00:11:42.464
Apostasize from the truth.

00:11:42.304 --> 00:11:44.960
If deserted by the spirit of God.

00:11:46.528 --> 00:11:49.344
The world never helps the church.

00:11:49.408 --> 00:11:51.904
It is all in arms against it.

00:11:51.840 --> 00:11:56.800
There is nothing in the world's air or soil that can fertilize the church.

00:11:56.864 --> 00:11:58.784
Even to the least degree.

00:11:59.328 --> 00:12:00.672
How is it then?

00:12:00.864 --> 00:12:03.488
That, notwithstanding all this,

00:12:03.680 --> 00:12:06.848
The church is a fair garden unto God.

00:12:06.880 --> 00:12:10.656
And there are sweet spices grown in its beds.

00:12:10.784 --> 00:12:15.616
And lovely flowers are gathered by the divine hand from its borders.

00:12:16.416 --> 00:12:18.080
The continuance

00:12:17.824 --> 00:12:21.632
And prosperity of the church can only be accounted for

00:12:21.376 --> 00:12:23.392
By supposing him,

00:12:23.424 --> 00:12:24.896
To be the gardener.

00:12:25.728 --> 00:12:33.472
Almighty strength is put to the otherwise impossible work of sustaining a holy people among men.

00:12:33.856 --> 00:12:40.192
Almighty wisdom exercises itself upon this otherwise insuperable difficulty.

00:12:40.800 --> 00:12:42.944
Hear ye the word of the Lord.

00:12:42.944 --> 00:12:46.720
And learn the reason for the growth of his church below.

00:12:47.232 --> 00:12:49.728
I the Lord do keep it.

00:12:49.984 --> 00:12:52.544
I will water it every moment.

00:12:52.480 --> 00:12:54.304
Lest any hurt it.

00:12:54.304 --> 00:12:56.992
I will keep it night and day.

00:12:57.536 --> 00:13:02.624
That is the reason for the existence of a spiritual people still.

00:13:02.496 --> 00:13:05.760
In the midst of a godless and perverse generation.

00:13:06.048 --> 00:13:09.504
This is the reason for an election of grace.

00:13:09.440 --> 00:13:12.032
In the midst of surrounding vice,

00:13:11.808 --> 00:13:13.632
And worldliness,

00:13:13.408 --> 00:13:15.008
And unbelief.

00:13:15.552 --> 00:13:17.344
Supposing him,

00:13:17.056 --> 00:13:18.848
to be the gardener

00:13:18.656 --> 00:13:21.952
I can see why there should be fruitfulness.

00:13:22.016 --> 00:13:23.200
And beauty.

00:13:23.136 --> 00:13:27.488
And sweetness, even in the centre of the wilderness of sin.

00:13:28.256 --> 00:13:32.288
Another mystery is also cleared up by this supposition.

00:13:32.896 --> 00:13:34.656
The wonder is...

00:13:34.464 --> 00:13:38.848
That you and I should have been placed among the plants of the Lord.

00:13:39.264 --> 00:13:43.360
Why are we allowed to grow in the garden of his grace?

00:13:43.232 --> 00:13:45.664
Why me, Lord? Why me?

00:13:45.888 --> 00:13:47.040
How is it?

00:13:46.880 --> 00:13:48.960
That we have been kept there,

00:13:48.896 --> 00:13:50.528
And born with.

00:13:50.336 --> 00:13:52.128
In our barrenness

00:13:52.160 --> 00:13:55.168
When he might long ago have said, cut it down.

00:13:55.136 --> 00:13:57.376
Why cumber is it the ground?

00:13:58.080 --> 00:14:02.176
Who else would have borne with such waywardness as ours?

00:14:02.496 --> 00:14:06.176
Who could have manifested such infinite patience?

00:14:06.560 --> 00:14:09.728
Who would have tended us with such care?

00:14:09.856 --> 00:14:12.576
And when the care was so ill rewarded,

00:14:12.512 --> 00:14:16.352
Who would have renewed it so long from day to day?

00:14:16.608 --> 00:14:20.192
And persisted in designs of boundless love.

00:14:20.736 --> 00:14:23.264
Who could have done more for his vineyard?

00:14:23.328 --> 00:14:25.280
Who could or would?

00:14:25.024 --> 00:14:26.752
Have done so much.

00:14:27.360 --> 00:14:31.040
Any mere man would have repented of his good intent.

00:14:30.880 --> 00:14:33.504
Provoked by our ingratitude.

00:14:34.048 --> 00:14:35.552
None but God.

00:14:35.552 --> 00:14:38.400
Could have had patience with some of us.

00:14:39.168 --> 00:14:44.352
That we have not long ago been slipped off as fruitless branches of the vine,

00:14:44.256 --> 00:14:47.168
That we are left still upon the stem.

00:14:47.008 --> 00:14:52.128
In the hope that we may ultimately bring forth fruit is a great marvel.

00:14:53.024 --> 00:14:57.856
I know not how it is that we have been spared except upon this ground.

00:14:57.856 --> 00:14:59.456
Supposing him?

00:14:59.520 --> 00:15:01.024
to be the gardener.

00:15:02.048 --> 00:15:05.280
For Jesus is all gentleness and grace.

00:15:05.312 --> 00:15:07.488
So slow with his knife.

00:15:07.616 --> 00:15:09.152
So tardy!

00:15:08.960 --> 00:15:10.432
With his axe.

00:15:10.432 --> 00:15:11.840
So hopeful.

00:15:11.968 --> 00:15:14.464
If we do but show a bud or two.

00:15:14.528 --> 00:15:15.968
Or perchance,

00:15:15.808 --> 00:15:18.496
Yield a little sour berry.

00:15:18.784 --> 00:15:20.800
So hopeful, I say!

00:15:20.512 --> 00:15:24.736
That these may be hopeful predictions of something better.

00:15:24.608 --> 00:15:25.792
Bye and bye.

00:15:26.272 --> 00:15:28.416
Infinite patience.

00:15:28.736 --> 00:15:31.104
Immeasurable long-suffering.

00:15:31.968 --> 00:15:34.048
Where are you to be found?

00:15:33.824 --> 00:15:36.512
But in the breast of the well-beloved.

00:15:37.248 --> 00:15:40.832
Surely the gardener's hoe has spared many of us.

00:15:40.640 --> 00:15:45.632
Simply and only because he who is meek and lowly in heart

00:15:46.048 --> 00:15:47.392
is the God-man.

00:15:48.928 --> 00:15:55.904
Thank you for listening, friends. this podcast was brought to you by Premier in association with Spurgeon's College.

00:15:55.872 --> 00:15:59.488
For more Christian podcasts, sermons, and music,

00:15:59.392 --> 00:16:04.416
Head back to the website premier.plus and sign in for free.

00:16:10.336 --> 00:16:20.384
Leprosy still exists. Every two minutes someone is diagnosed with this disease. In an unjust world their suffering won't make the headlines. It's hidden in the world's poor world.

00:16:19.904 --> 00:16:29.952
Old, poorest places. The physical effects are devastating. But the hardest part is how you are treated. Even if you've been cured, you can be rejected by your family and community.

00:16:29.472 --> 00:16:39.520
isolated, shamed and forgotten. But God sees and so do we. It's time to end leprosy. To learn more, visit leprosymission.org.uk/support

00:16:39.040 --> 00:16:40.672
2k slash premiere.
